# CQRS — <%= appName %>

Command Query Responsibility Segregation is enabled for this project.

## Layout

- `src/cqrs/` — CommandBus, QueryBus, EventBus, middleware, handler registration
- `src/application/commands/` — write-side commands + handlers
- `src/application/queries/` — read-side queries + handlers
- `src/application/events/` — integration/domain events

## Usage

```ts
import { commandBus, queryBus, registerCqrsHandlers } from './src/cqrs/index.js';
import { CreateUserCommand } from './src/application/commands/CreateUserCommand.js';
import { GetUserQuery } from './src/application/queries/GetUserQuery.js';

registerCqrsHandlers();

const user = await commandBus.execute(new CreateUserCommand('demo@example.com'));
const found = await queryBus.execute(new GetUserQuery(user.id));
```

## Generate more

```bash
my make command create-order
my make query list-orders
```

## Middleware

Logging and validation middleware are registered in `register-handlers.ts`. Extend with your own validators or cross-cutting concerns.
